Union Cafe is an "All You Care To Eat" concept that features daily rotating specials made from scratch. You pay one price to the cashier before entering the restaurant, and once in the dining room, you are able to return as often as you would like during your stay. This gives a unique experience where our guests are able to sample offerings from many different platforms and enjoy a unique experience each meal. We look forward to seeing you!

2018-2019 Union Cafe Door Pricing
Breakfast: $7.60
Brunch: $9.80
Lunch: $9.80
Dinner: $11.25

Vegetarian: Contains no meat, fish, poultry, shellfish or products derived from these sources but may contain dairy or eggs
Vegan: Contains absolutely no animal or dairy products.
Made without Gluten-Containing Ingredients: does not contain ingredients that are sources of gluten, but is prepared in an open kitchen where gluten is present.
Farm to Fork: Contains seasonal, minimally processed ingredients from a local farm, ranch, or fishing boat.
Seafood Watch: Contains seafood that meets the Monterey Bay Aquarium's Seafood Watch guidelines for commercial buyers.

Eat Right — For You

Do you care about whether your food was grown locally or raised humanely? Or are you more interested in protein vs. carbs?

Whatever your priorities, we can help you chew the right thing. At Bon Appétit, we’re working toward “food service for a sustainable future.” How we define that is a mouthful, but the bottom line is that we strive to cook delicious food that’s good for you, the animals, the workers, the community, and the Earth — because they’re all connected. And we’re proud to be the first food service company to tackle many important issues in these areas.

We’re here to support you by giving the information you need to choose wisely. Visit our Wellness page for a feast of information about the roles our from-scratch cooking, nutritional approach, local sourcing, and other sustainability programs can play on your menu.

Food Recovery Verified

Bon Appétit at Rose-Hulman is fighting food waste and hunger by  recovering surplus perishable food from our campus that would  otherwise go to waste and donating it to people in need through The Catholic Charities Terre Haute Food Bank

Nutrition Facts Tables

We understand that many guests desire more specific nutrition facts information. To help you check the nutritional values of many of our basic café offerings, Bon Appétit has compiled This Online Guide

Please note that not all of these items are served on our menu each day.

Well-Being Indicator®

The Well-Being Indicator ® represents more than just numbers. It gives you a quick, at-a-glance visual that puts nutrition into an overall context of health.

Because we care about your well-being, Bon Appétit Management Company is partnering with Rose-Hulman Institute of Technology to launch a new, holistic nutrition program that makes it easy to find the healthful options in the café.
